1.title: Steve Zastrow/Burlap Wolf King/Jami Lynn/Condor/The Tinder Box
1.plot: This Pilot Episode features the acts of Steve Zastrow, Thomas Hentges recording as Burlap Wolf King, Jami Lynn, Condor, and The Tinder Box.

2.title: T. Wilson King/Jeff Thomson/Joe Fokken/Mat D with Kurt Mullins/Chad Elliott with Bonita Crowe
2.plot: On this weeks episode White Wall Sessions features the artists T. Wilson King, Jeff Thomson, Joe Fokken, Mat D with Kurt Mullins, and Chad Elliott with Bonita Crowe.

3.title: John Goraj/Copoetics/Amos Slade/Hometown Glow
3.plot: This weeks episode features John Goraj, Dan Finch and Louisa Mae of Copoetics, Nick Engbers of Amos Slade, and Hometown Glow.

4.title: Billy Lurken/Ryan Kickland/Dylan James/We Live in Sod Houses/The Tinder Box
4.plot: This week we showcase the talents of Billy Lurken, Ryan Kickland, Dylan James, Dustin and Rachael DeBoer along with Steve Carlson and Josh Rieck all from We Live in Sod Houses, as well as Chad Konrad Jon Wallner and Dominic Osterloh from The Tinder Box.

5.title: Joe Fokken/Jami Lynn & Dylan James/Mat D with Kurt Mullins/Burlap Wolf King
5.plot: This week we feature Joe Fokken, Jami Lynn and Dylan James, Mat D with Kurt Mullins, and Thomas Hentges as Burlap Wolf King.

6.title: High Wine/New Moon Shine/Jack, Johnny & Jamison/Union Grove Pickers/Charlie Parr
6.plot: This week we are joined by Xavier Pastrano (Vocals, Guitar, Kickbox) Emily Jelen (Vocals, Percussion) and Aaron Clark (Bass) from High Wine. They play "live for misery". Sean McFarland (Guitar/Vocals) Laurie Brown (Vocals) Roy Haberstick (Bass) and Charlie Anderson (Mandolin) of New Moonshine play "european cities". Jack, Johnny, Jamison is made up of Jack Rollins (Guitar/Vocals) Johnny Berkness (Guitar/Vocals) Travis Jamison (Bass) and Connor Pederson (Mandolin) play Jack, Johnny and Jamison and Son. imdb.plot outline: The White Wall Sessions showcases local, regional and national music acts performing original acoustic, americana, bluegrass, folk and blues in a laid back, intimate setting. The White Wall Sessions is recorded in a small studio in Sioux Falls, SD. From it's inception, the show was intended to be a visual and audio experience that takes the viewer a bit further into each performance. The program is recorded in full 1080p HD and utilizes state of the art production and post production equipment. Every song is tracked live and completely remixed. We take an artistic, documentary-like visual feel to each song, which gives the viewer a personal, introspective look at each musician and song. The songs are intended to be offered to the viewer as a moment in time. A moment in time we felt needed to be captured. We take a look into the music of people who are passionate, dedicated and who are committed to their art.
